title: How's China addressing low fertility problem? 'Love education' is the answer

description: Anmol Bishnoi, brother of jailed gangster Lawrence Bishnoi, is identified as the main conspirator in NCP leader Baba Siddique's murder. Mumbai Police, invoking MCOCA, arrested eight suspects and sought further investigation. Anmol provided financial support and communicated with co-accused. The court granted police custody until 7 December.
title: Baba Siddique murder: Lawrence Bishnoi's brother Anmol main conspirator

description: PAN card holders can update their addresses for free and receive an e-PAN with a QR code via email. They can also request a physical copy for Rs 50. The initiative, PAN 2.0, aims to digitise the PAN and TAN administration system for better taxpayer services.
title: PAN 2.0 for free! How to get PAN Card with QR code - step-by-step guide

description: India, despite their previous poor show, enter the second Test of the Border-Gavaskar Trophy with confidence after a big win in Perth. The Adelaide Oval pitch is expected to be balanced, offering assistance to both bowlers and batters, making the upcoming day-night Test an intriguing contest. The second Test begins on December 6.
title: Adelaide pitch curator's advice to India, Australia

description: A man, his wife, and their daughter were discovered murdered in their South Delhi home on Wednesday morning. Their son, returning from a morning walk, found them and notified the police. No signs of ransacking or theft were evident. A case has been registered, and an investigation is ongoing.
title: South Delhi horror: Man, his wife and daughter found murdered in Neb Sarai

description: Shoaib Akhtar believes India is more eager to play in Pakistan than vice versa, emphasizing that Virat Kohli is particularly keen. Despite the ICC Champions Trophy matches being relocated to Dubai for Indian teams, Akhtar urges Pakistan to adopt a positive stance towards future tournaments in India. PCB demands equal hybrid model terms for ICC events held in India.
title: 'Agar India, Pakistan land kar jaati toh...' says Shoaib Akhtar

description: Practice sessions for the Indian cricket team will no longer be open to the public during the rest of the Border-Gavaskar Trophy. The decision follows disturbances caused by loud chants and comments from fans during their training in Adelaide on December 3, which affected their preparation for the pink-ball Test starting December 6.
title: Fans barred from India nets sessions after heckling

description: KL Rahul found form while opening batting in Rohit Sharma's absence during the Perth Test against Australia. With Rohit back, questions arise about Rahul's batting position in the Adelaide Test. Rahul responded humorously about the decision, opting to keep his cards close to the chest. The pink-ball match at the Adelaide Oval begins on December 6.
title: KL Rahul's cheeky reply to 'at what position will you bat'

description: Ben Stokes was left bemused over the ICC's over-rate penalties imposed on England after their win against New Zealand, leading to the deduction of World Test Championship points. England and New Zealand were penalised for slow over-rates in the first Test.
title: Ben Stokes lashes out at ICC after England, NZ penalised

description: Bhim Singh's reappearance after decades, believed to be alive by a grieving Ghaziabad family, is unraveling as another family in Sikar and Dehradun reports similar encounters. Tularam has opted for a DNA test to confirm Bhim's identity, causing a household divide. Police await results to proceed with further investigations, while suspicions rise about Bhim's true story.
title: ‘Serial son’ had made miracle return to Rajasthan family also

description: Amid uncertainty over Maharashtra's new chief minister, posters suggesting Devendra Fadnavis as the frontrunner were seen in Mumbai. A significant BJP meeting is set to decide the leader, who will stake a claim to form the government. Preparations for the swearing-in ceremony at Azad Maidan are underway, with several VVIPs, including the Prime Minister, expected to attend.
title: Amid suspense, posters put up in Mumbai declaring Fadnavis Maha CM

description: Jiohotstar.com has been officially transferred to Viacom18 Media Pvt. Ltd., a subsidiary of Reliance Industries, confirming Reliance's ownership. The domain, originally owned by a Delhi-based engineer and later transferred to Dubai siblings, faced legal and commercial disputes, now resolved. Manish Painuly from Viacom18 is the current registrant and administrative contact.
title: Mukesh Ambani's Viacom 18 finally gets rights of JioHotstar after month-long drama

description: Eknath Shinde asked BJP to make him CM for six months if not for the full term, but BJP rejected, saying it would set a bad precedent. BJP insisted on keeping the CM post as they had a near-clear majority in the state assembly. Shinde agreed to accept any decision by BJP leadership.
title: 'At Shah meeting, Shinde asked to be made CM for at least first 6 months'

description: A hardline Sikh activist attempted to assassinate former deputy chief minister Sukhbir Singh Badal at the Golden Temple by opening fire. A swift-acting sewadar prevented the shooting by deflecting the attacker's arm. Sukhbir continued his religious duties despite the ordeal. The attacker was identified but police have not officially confirmed it.
title: How alert 'sewadar' saved life of Sukhbir Singh Badal at Golden Temple

description: Sunil Gavaskar, Sachin Tendulkar, and Virat Kohli, each excelled in their cricketing eras, making unique contributions to the sport. Gavaskar's performances against fast bowlers without helmets, Tendulkar's versatility across formats, and Kohli's excellence in modern cricket are highlighted. Gavaskar humorously cites Sir Gary Sobers as the best cricketer during a talk show.
title: Sunil Gavaskar vs Sachin Tendulkar vs Virat Kohli: And the verdict is...

description: The UK government has updated its travel advisory for Bangladesh due to potential terrorist threats and attacks on religious minorities. The advisory warns against non-essential travel to specific regions and urges caution around police buildings and large gatherings. British officials are closely monitoring the situation, with diplomatic efforts in place to address concerns and ensure the protection of minority communities in Bangladesh.
title: 'Terrorists likely to carry out attacks': UK issues advisory for B'desh

description: Mark Zuckerberg, Meta CEO, aims to influence technology policy in a potential Trump administration, with a focus on artificial intelligence. This comes after a recent dinner meeting with Trump. Meta's president of global affairs acknowledged past content moderation errors, signaling a strategic shift to favorably align with Trump.
title: Zuckerberg wants to go the 'Elon Musk way' in Donald Trump govt

description: South Korea faced a political crisis when President Yoon Suk Yeol declared martial law, leading to massive protests and a swift reversal by the parliament. Troops surrounded the National Assembly, but lawmakers managed to convene and vote against the decree. Yoon's decision has been widely condemned, evoking memories of past authoritarianism.
title: Martial law shocker: Six hours that jolted South Korea, what's next

description: An earthquake measuring 5.3 on the Richter scale strikes Mulugu district in Telangana, causing tremors across multiple regions including Hyderabad. The tremor's epicentre is identified in the Medaram region, with no immediate damage reported. The quake, recorded at a 40-kilometre depth, lasted between 6 to 10 seconds.
title: Watch: Scary visuals show moment 5.3-magnitude quake hit Telangana's Mulugu
Man opens fire at SAD leader Sukhbir Singh Badal at Golden Temple in Amritsar

description: A Virginia man, Naresh Bhatt, has been charged with the murder of his wife, Mamta Bhatt, who disappeared four months ago. Naresh allegedly researched how long it takes to remarry after a spouse's death. Her DNA was linked to blood found in their home. Mamta's disappearance has drawn significant community and international attention.
title: Man who Googled 'how to remarry after spouse die' charged for wife's murder
These airlines saw the most delays and complaints in 2024

description: Uttar Pradesh police increased security in several districts as Rahul Gandhi and Congress MPs plan to visit Sambhal. Prohibitory orders are extended till December 31. The district administration denied their visit after November 24 clashes led to deaths and injuries, including police personnel, during a court-mandated survey of the Jama Masjid, claimed to be originally a temple.
title: Rahul to visit Sambhal, cops prepare for round 2 of showdown with Congress

description: Pakistan's Sufiyan Muqeem shone in the T20I against Zimbabwe with an impressive five-wicket haul, leading to a series-clinching 10-wicket victory. Zimbabwe collapsed to 57 all out, with only two batters reaching double figures. Pakistan secured the win rapidly, thanks to strong performances from Saim Ayub and Omair Yousuf. The series concludes on Thursday.
title: Another clash with Zimbabwe, another record set in Pakistan cricket

description: Adelaide Oval curator Damian Hough is preparing for possible rain and storms on the first day of the second Test between Australia and India. The pitch will have 6mm of grass, the same as the recent Sheffield Shield match. A sell-out crowd is expected as Australia hope to rebound from a heavy defeat in Perth.
title: Adelaide pitch curator braces for rain-impacted start

description: Harbhajan Singh reveals he no longer speaks to MS Dhoni despite their shared history in cricket, including playing together for Team India and the Chennai Super Kings in the IPL. Harbhajan notes the lack of personal interaction and Dhoni's unresponsiveness to his calls, suggesting there might be unspoken reasons for their limited communication.
title: I don't speak to MS Dhoni, says Harbhajan Singh

description: US Congressman Brad Sherman stresses that Bangladesh's interim government must protect its Hindu minority and address their grievances amidst violent unrest. An urgent call for investigation by the UN highlights the concern. Protests continued near the White House, demanding freedom for Hindu monk Chinmoy Krishna Brahmachari, who faces life threats in custody.
title: US Congressman lawmaker calls for protection of Hindus in B'desh

description: 'Pushpa 2: The Rule', directed by Sukumar and starring Allu Arjun, is setting new records with its advance bookings, amassing an estimated Rs 62.21 crore for the opening day. With predictions of over Rs 200 crore for the opening weekend, it aims to surpass previous benchmarks in Indian cinema. The film releases on December 4 across multiple languages.
title: 'Pushpa 2: The Rule' smashes advance booking records
7.8% polling in Maha after 5pm not a surge, equals avg turnout: CEO data
No lawyer shows up for monk in Bangladesh court

description: India's first training session under lights in Adelaide drew huge crowds, as players adjusted to the challenging pink ball conditions ahead of the crucial second Test against Australia. While fans enjoyed the spectacle, the team grappled with strategic decisions, particularly around opening positions, as they looked to consolidate their series advantage.
title: 2nd Test: Adelaide tickled pink by Team India's presence
Earthquake of 5.3 magnitude hits Telangana

description: US President-elect Donald Trump's legal team has filed a motion seeking to dismiss his hush money conviction, arguing it disrupts presidential duties and undermines voters' mandate. The case involves 34 counts of falsifying business records related to a payment to Stormy Daniels. Trump's lawyers claim the prosecution is politically motivated and seek to delay sentencing until 2029.
title: Donald Trump’s legal team moves to dismiss hush money case

description: Sachin Tendulkar and Vinod Kambli reunited to unveil their late coach Ramakant Achrekar's memorial in Mumbai on his birth anniversary. The reunion brought back memories of their partnership from their school days before they became India teammates. But while Tendulkar went on become a cricket icon, Kambli's career ended early because of various reasons.
title: Vinod Kambli sings a song, Sachin Tendulkar claps - Watch

description: A Delaware judge has once again rejected Elon Musk's $101bn pay package from Tesla, citing excessive influence on the board and unfairness to shareholders. Despite shareholder approval, the decision stands, impacting Musk's access to the compensation while Tesla plans to appeal the ruling.
title: World's richest man is fighting for his salary, and he loses yet again

description: Hundreds of students at Uday Pratap College in Varanasi recited Hanuman Chalisa near a campus mosque, reigniting a controversy over the land's ownership after a large number of Muslims offered namaz. The UP Sunni Central Waqf Board clarified that their 2018 claim on the land had already been cancelled in 2021.
title: Students recite Hanuman Chalisa near mosque on Varanasi college campus

description: Bhim Singh, who has appeared after allegedly being in captivity for three decades, is at the center of a mystery, living with multiple families who believe he is their lost son. Police are conducting a DNA test to determine his identity, with results expected within a week. His story remains puzzling as more families come forward.
title: Before Gzb & Dehradun, same ‘son’ made miracle return to Raj family
Centre clears 5 projects for Rs 21,772 crore military upgrade
Bhutan king to visit India tomorrow, will meet PM Modi
Biden nod for $1.1bn sale of logistics for naval choppers
After maths, CBSE to bring 2-tier system for science, social science
Foreign students in India at record high after Covid tumble

description: A Congress delegation raised concerns with the Election Commission over anomalies in Maharashtra electoral rolls and post-poll voter turnout surge. The EC responded with clarifications, noting additions matched population growth and deletions were minimal. Procedural formalities caused the voter turnout gap. The EC urged Congress to raise objections during the draft roll scrutiny.
title: EC replies to Cong concerns on Maha voters' list, turnout

description: Tata Group Chairman N Chandrasekaran has urged group company CEOs to pursue growth aggressively despite economic challenges, emphasizing large-scale ambitious targets and short-term margin adjustments. Key investments focus on Tata Electronics, Air India, and Tata Digital, with an aim for top 10 business status in the next three years.
title: Tata Group chairman to group CEOs: 'Cyclical quarters can be no ...'

description: Sunil Pal was missing for several hours after a show, leading his wife to file a missing person complaint. Police later found him, and his wife confirmed he is safe but disturbed. Sunil Pal is known for his comedy career, winning The Great Indian Laughter Challenge in 2005 and acting in Bollywood films.
title: Exclusive - Sunil Pal's wife Sarita confirms that the comedian has been traced; says 'Police is helping us'

description: InterGlobe Aviation, owner of IndiGo, has filed a lawsuit against Mahindra Electric Automobiles for trademark infringement over the '6E' mark. Mahindra plans to launch an electric SUV named BE 6e, which IndiGo claims might confuse consumers. Both companies are discussing a resolution, with IndiGo emphasizing the strong global recognition of its '6E' mark.
title: Why India's largest airline & one of the biggest auto co are 'fighting'

description: British Tory MP Bob Blackman described the violence against Hindus in Bangladesh as an attempt at ethnic cleansing. In the House of Commons debate, MPs expressed concern over safety and called for UK action. Over 2,000 violent incidents since August have targeted Hindus, sparking calls for international intervention and accountability from Bangladesh’s authorities.
title: Violence in B’desh ‘attempt at ethnic cleansing of Hindus’: UK MP
